== rylyz player service
This Service Provides:
o Socket Services (Pusher) for wyjyts
o rylyz openApp javascript framework

== Start this service on port 80
--> $ sudo apachectl stop
--> $ rvmsudo rails server -p 80

Running on port 80 leverages the benefits of websockets
When running locally, turn off your default webserver.


== /etc/hosts
For dev environment: add the following to your /etc/hosts file

127.0.0.1       rylyz-player.heroku.com
127.0.0.1       rylyz-wyjyt.herokuapp.com


== Architecture 
When socket requests come in, the listeners will route the request to
the app server running on localhost but on a different port.
This service will make get request to localhost that look something like this:
HTTParty.get('http://127.0.0.1:8000/openapp/load', :query => {:game => "connect-4"})

== configure your  wyjyt.js
You can set the wyjyt.js file to look something like this:
<---------------------------------------
var  rylyzPlayerHost = "http://rylyz-player.heroku.com";

var  wyjytHost = 'http://rylyz-wyjyt.herokuapp.com';      //<- for deployment on heroku
var  wyjytHost ='http://rylyz-wyjyt.herokuapp.com:8888';  // <-- for local deployment (just don't push up to heroku !)

---------------------------------------->
